# Cloudflare Pages response headers (consumed at deploy).
#
# Pages defaults assets to `max-age=0, must-revalidate`, so every repeat visit
# re-validates EVERY sample file — a few hundred round trips (~50s) on a second
# load even though nothing changed. Sample media is immutable at a given path (a
# re-seed writes new dated session folders = new URLs), so cache it for a year.
#
# The pattern is `:session/*`, NOT `/samples/*`, and that matters: Pages APPENDS
# every matching rule's headers rather than letting a more specific rule win, so
# a `/samples/*` rule plus a `/samples/manifest.json` rule yields one spliced
# `Cache-Control: ...immutable, ...must-revalidate` and the browser honours the
# first directives it parses — pinning the manifest for a year. A `:session`
# placeholder matches exactly one segment, so this covers the media (always
# >=2 segments deep) and never touches /samples/manifest.json, which keeps the
# Pages default and stays revalidating so a future re-seed is picked up.
/samples/:session/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
